article.headline: Sacred Heart 75, Albany 69
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- James Samuels had 19 points to lead Sacred Heart past Albany 75-69 Saturday afternoon. Sacred Heart (4-4), holding a 35-34 halftime edge, took a 65-64 lead with 2:33 to play on a 3-pointer by Maurice Bailey and never looked back. Bailey and Kibwe Trim scored 15 points each for the Pioneers, while Justin James had 11. Trim also added 11 rebounds. Levi Levine led the Great Danes (1-5) with 22 points and eight rebounds, while Janis Pipikis had 18 points and Jon Iati had 16.
